'''Beverly Hanson''' (born December 5, 1924)<ref name=who>{{cite book |last=Elliott |first=Len |coauthors=Barbara Kelly |title=Who's Who in Golf |origyear=1976 |publisher=Arlington House |location=New Rochelle, New York |isbn=0870002252 |pages=81<U+2013>2 }}</ref><ref name=lpga>[http://www.lpga.com/content/oldplayerbios/HansonBeverlyFinal.pdf LPGA Tour biography]</ref> is an [[United states|American]] professional [[golf]]er who played on the United States-based [[LPGA Tour]]. 

Hanson was born in [[Fargo, North Dakota]].<ref name=who/><ref name=lpga/> She studied at the [[University of North Dakota]], [[Mills College]] in [[Oakland, California]] and the [[University of Wisconsin]]<ref name=lpga/> and was a [[bassoon]] player, performing with civic [[orchestra]]s. As an amateur golfer, she won the Texas Open in 1949 and both the California and Southern California ladies' championships. She was a member of the 1950 U.S. [[Curtis Cup]] golf team<ref name=who/> and that year won the [[United States Women's Amateur Golf Championship|U.S. Women's Amateur]].<ref name=who/>

In 1951, Hanson turned professional and won the very first event she competed in. She won the inaugural [[LPGA Championship]] in 1955,<ref name=who/> defeating [[Louise Suggs]]. In 1958 she was the [[LPGA leading money winners|leading money winner]] on the [[LPGA Tour]]. 

Hanson had 17 career wins on the LPGA Tour<ref>[http://www.lpga.com/content/All-timeWinnersList.pdf LPGA All-Time Winners List]</ref> of which three were [[women's majors|majors]]. Besides the inaugural LPGA major title, in 1956 she won the [[Women's Western Open]] and in 1958 the [[Titleholders Championship]].

Hanson lives part time in [[La Quinta, California]], and part time in [[Sun Valley, Idaho]].{{fact|date=September 2011}}

==Professional wins (18)==
===LPGA Tour wins (17)===
*[[1950 LPGA Tour|1950]] (1) [[Women's Texas Open]] (as an amateur)
*[[1951 LPGA Tour|1951]] (1) [[Eastern Women's Open|Eastern Open]]
*[[1953 LPGA Tour|1953]] (1) [[Boca Raton Weathervane]]
*[[1954 LPGA Tour|1954]] (2) [[St. Petersburg Women's Open|St. Petersburg Open]], [[Wichita Open (LPGA Tour)|Wichita Open]]
*[[1955 LPGA Tour|1955]] (2) '''[[LPGA Championship]]''', [[Battle Creek Open]]
*[[1956 LPGA Tour|1956]] (1) '''[[Women's Western Open]]'''
*[[1957 LPGA Tour|1957]] (2) [[Smokey Open]], [[Land of Sky Open]]
*[[1958 LPGA Tour|1958]] (2) '''[[Titleholders Championship]]''', [[Lawton Open]]
*[[1959 LPGA Tour|1959]] (4) [[Golden Triangle Festival]], [[American Women's Open]], [[Spokane Open]], [[Links Invitation Open]]
*[[1960 LPGA Tour|1960]] (1) [[St. Petersburg Women's Open|St. Petersburg Open]]

===Other wins (1)===
*1949 [[Women's Texas Open]] (as an amateur)
*1955 Hot Springs 4-Ball Invitational (with [[Kathy Cornelius]])

